AT the farewell celebration for Miss South Africa, Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters, friends, family and sponsors gathered for the viewing of her national dress. This is one of the two dresses she will wear as she represents the country at Miss Universe. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  The event took place at the Altitude Champagne Bar at Menlyn Maine in Pretoria. Miss Universe 2017 will be the 66th Miss Universe pageant to be held on November 26 at The AXIS in Las Vegas, Nevada, United States. Iris Mittenaere of France will crown her successor at the end of the event.